alerts.description:
Information on update: The warning area has been expanded, notably to cover more of southeast England and East Anglia. Not everywhere will experience fog, but where fog patches do develop, they are likely to become dense in some places with visibility less than 100 metres, and perhaps less than 50 metres in a few spots. 

The fog will slowly thin towards late morning but may persist into the afternoon in some areas. For further details see https://www.metoffice.gov.uk/weather/warnings-and-advice/uk-warnings
